    "body": "I've also tweaked logging so that messages at level WARNING or above get the level name in the message.  The one thing I don't like about this is that our `--existing` message uses the 'CRITICAL' log level, to ensure it gets printed.  I do not think this is really appropriate.  What do people think about switching the log level of the `--existing` message to INFO and/or switching it to plain `io.rprint`?\n"
